# V10 pseudo-label pipeline (stage-1 = the component of LB-best 0.97998).
# At tau=0.98 keeps 226k/270k test rows, pseudo-labels from recipe_full_te
# argmax. Retrained XGB on real+pseudo. Essential for downstream blending
# since the current LB-best submission is 50/50 log-blend with recipe.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_recipe_pseudolabel.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_recipe_pseudolabel.npy
# Stage-2 pseudo-label (labeler = LB-best blend). OOF-overfit on the
# training folds, LB null despite OOF lift. Kept for cross-session
# confirmation that self-refinement saturates at this labeler strength.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_recipe_pseudolabel_stage2.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_recipe_pseudolabel_stage2.npy
# recipe_allpairs (cat x cat + cat x num = 116 pairs, 795 features).
# Errors 9,938 (LOWEST of any variant) + Jaccard 0.81 vs recipe —
# satisfies both "Jaccard < 0.80 AND err <= anchor" blend heuristics
# without OOF-overfit. Contributes +0.00020 in 3-way blends.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_recipe_allpairs.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_recipe_allpairs.npy
# recipe_lgbm (LGBM mirror of recipe_full_te). Null blend leg (Jaccard
# 0.86 with XGB-recipe, near-identical error set). Kept for diagnostic.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_recipe_lgbm.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_recipe_lgbm.npy
# recipe_catboost (CatBoost mirror of recipe_full_te, CPU depth=4,
# l2=5, 3000 iter). Tuned OOF 0.97897, blend null under recipe bias
# (High-class calibration mismatch), but gets weight in 4-way greedy
# blends. Kept for blend-stack experiments.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_recipe_catboost.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_recipe_catboost.npy
# Stage-1 blend labeler = 50/50 log-blend of recipe + pseudo stage-1
# at recipe's tuned bias (= the test probs of LB-0.97998 submission).
# Used as labeler for stage-2 pseudo-label.
!scripts/artifacts/test_recipe_blend_stage1.npy
# Soft-target distillation student — XGB on recipe features trained with
# custom soft cross-entropy against 50/50 log-blend teacher (= LB-best).
# Standalone OOF tuned 0.98096 (+0.00084 over LB-best teacher). First
# own-pipeline lever to break the 0.97998 stacking-inflation ceiling.
# Errors 9,520 vs teacher's 9,851. Jaccard 0.7924 vs recipe, 0.8155 vs
# LB-best. Distillation regularizes + effectively ensembles teacher's
# 2 components into a smoother decision surface.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_soft_distill.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_soft_distill.npy
# Multi-seed pseudo-label: recipe_full_te at FOLD_SEED=7 (labeler source)
# + recipe_pseudolabel with seed7 labeler (target model at FOLD_SEED=42).
# Labeler's fold split is decoupled from target's - bypasses stage-2
# OOF-overfit mechanism.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_recipe_full_te_seed7.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_recipe_full_te_seed7.npy
!scripts/artifacts/oof_recipe_pseudolabel_seed7labeler.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_recipe_pseudolabel_seed7labeler.npy
!scripts/artifacts/recipe_pseudolabel_seed7labeler_results.json

# Cleanlab confident-learning diagnostic: per-row boolean mask of
# likely-noisy training rows, built from the LB-best 2-way blend as
# teacher. Diagnostic flagged 2,035 rows (0.32%), 98.4% precision vs
# rule-mismatch (the known 10,304 NN flips). Used as input mask for
# recipe_full_te CLEANLAB_TREATMENT ∈ {drop, downweight, relabel}
# interventions.
!scripts/artifacts/cleanlab_issues_prune_by_noise_rate.npy

# Saerens-2002 EM label-shift corrected posteriors on LB-best blend.
# EM-uniform OOF = 0.97969 (Δ -0.00043 vs recipe-bias baseline 0.98012);
# ties after bias re-tune. Test prior matches train prior (no label
# shift). A1 lever CLOSED as null — log-bias already near-Bayes-optimal.
# Kept for potential blend experiments.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_em_uniform.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_em_uniform.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_em_testprior.npy

# Cleanlab DROP variant: recipe_full_te retrained with 2,035 flagged
# training rows removed per fold. Tuned OOF 0.97965 (ties recipe; −0.00046
# vs LB-best). Has +336 more errors than LB-best + Jaccard 0.796 — fails
# blend heuristic (needs fewer errors AND Jaccard<0.80). Cleanlab lever
# CLOSED as null — flagged rows are deterministic NN-flip signal, not
# stochastic noise; removing them hurts model experience without gain.
# Kept for cross-branch diagnostic.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_recipe_full_te_cldrop.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_recipe_full_te_cldrop.npy

# C0 isotonic greedy outputs. Full greedy (0.98055 OOF) is dominated
# by soft_distill__iso which carries that component's +0.00246 LB
# regression — NOT for LB probe. Safe greedy (excludes soft_distill)
# lands at OOF 0.98026-0.98031 via recipe_pseudolabel_stage2 or
# recipe_allpairs__iso, below +0.00020 LB-transfer threshold.
# Reaffirms the 0.98030 stacking-inflation ceiling; kept for
# cross-branch diagnostic.
!scripts/artifacts/oof_c0_greedy.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_c0_greedy.npy
!scripts/artifacts/oof_c0_safe_recipe_full_te.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_c0_safe_recipe_full_te.npy
!scripts/artifacts/oof_c0_safe_lb_best_2way.npy
!scripts/artifacts/test_c0_safe_lb_best_2way.npy

